The paper describes a system for exploring and analyzing potential data sources for NLP techniques, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The use case of narrative descriptions of mobility information in clinical data also suggests a potential focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) for healthcare applications. The paper also mentions a web-based interface and modular backend, which suggests a potential focus on computer networks and distributed computing (CY). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computer Networks and Distributed Computing).
